# Monero

Call                                                                                | Description
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[xmr_get_block](#xmr_get_block)                                                     | Returns full block information by either block height or block hash.
[xmr_get_block_count](#xmr_get_block_count)                                         | Returns the current block height known to the node.
[xmr_get_block_header_by_hash](#xmr_get_block_header_by_hash)                       | Returns basic block information for a block hash.
[xmr_get_block_header_by_height](#xmr_get_block_header_by_height)                   | Returns basic block information for a block height.
[xmr_get_block_headers_range](#xmr_get_block_headers_range)                         | Returns basic block information retrieved for a range of block heights.
[xmr_get_fee_estimate](#xmr_get_fee_estimate)                                       | Returns an estimation on fees per byte.
[xmr_get_last_block_header](#xmr_get_last_block_header)                             | Returns the block header information for the most recent block.
[xmr_get_transaction_pool](#xmr_get_transaction_pool)                               | Returns valid transactions seen by the node, but not mined into a block.
[xmr_get_transaction_pool_stats](#xmr_get_transaction_pool_stats)                   | Returns the transaction pool stats.
[xmr_get_transactions](#xmr_get_transactions)                                       | Returns transaction information by hash.
[xmr_get_version](#xmr_get_version)                                                 | Returns the nodes current version.
[xmr_hard_fork_info](#xmr_hard_fork_info)                                           | Returns hard fork voting and readiness information.
[xmr_on_get_block_hash](#xmr_on_get_block_hash)                                     | Returns the block hash for a block height.
[xmr_send_raw_transaction](#xmr_send_raw_transaction)                               | Broadcast raw transaction to the network.





## xmr_get_block

> Sample Data

```cli
{
  "block_height": "1999263",
  "block_hash": "de3a7a44253774c7c63ed153d129a502294ec19a542d83b462ceccc18673fb90"
}
```
Returns full block information by either block height or block hash.


### Request Parameters

> Sample Request

```shell
curl -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '["de3a7a44253774c7c63ed153d129a502294ec19a542d83b462ceccc18673fb90"]' https://api.oracleminer.com/xrs/xmr_get_block
```

```plaintext
blocknet-cli xrService xmr_get_block 1999263
```
<code class="api-call">xmr_get_block [block_height] or [block_hash]</code>

Parameter       | Type       | Description
----------------|------------|-------------
block_height    | int        | The block's height.
block_hash      | string     | The block's hash.

## xmr_get_block_count

Returns the current block height known to the node.

### Request Parameters

> Sample Request

```shell
curl -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '[]' https://api.oracleminer.com/xrs/xmr_get_block_count
```

```plaintext
blocknet-cli xrService xmr_get_block_count
```
<code class="api-call">xmr_get_block_count</code>

This call does not take parameters.


### Response

<aside class="success">
200 OK
</aside>

> Sample 200 Response

```shell
{
  "count": 2091023,
  "status": "OK",
  "untrusted": false
}
```

```plaintext
{
  "reply": {
    "count": 1999273,
    "status": "OK",
    "untrusted": false
  },
  "uuid": "B15AA753-4B57-44E3-AB9F-63C2FA60926E"
}
```

Parameter            | Type          | Description
---------------------|---------------|-------------
count                | int           | Number of blocks in longest chain seen by the node.
status               | string        | RPC error code.
untrusted            | boolean       | Obtained results from bootstrap mode is not trusted (`true`), otherwise trusted (`false`).
uuid                 | string        | The response ID, which can be used to view this response again with [xrGetReply](https://api.blocknet.co/#xrgetreply).

## xmr_get_version

Returns the nodes current version.

### Request Parameters

> Sample Request

```shell
curl -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '[]' https://api.oracleminer.com/xrs/xmr_get_version
```

```plaintext
blocknet-cli xrService xmr_get_version
```
<code class="api-call">xmr_get_version</code>

This call does not take parameters.


### Response

<aside class="success">
200 OK
</aside>

> Sample 200 Response

```shell
{
  "release": true,
  "status": "OK",
  "untrusted": false,
  "version": 196608
}
```

```plaintext
{
  "reply": {
    "release": true,
    "status": "OK",
    "untrusted": false,
    "version": 196608
  },
  "uuid": "D284C607-5953-4374-A71D-897B1F795E86"
}
```

Parameter            | Type          | Description
---------------------|---------------|-------------
release              | boolean       | If release (`true`), otherwise (`false`).
status               | string        | RPC error code.
untrusted            | boolean       | Obtained results from bootstrap mode is not trusted (`true`), otherwise trusted (`false`).
version              | int           | Version number.
uuid                 | string        | The response ID, which can be used to view this response again with [xrGetReply](https://api.blocknet.co/#xrgetreply).





## xmr_hard_fork_info

Returns hard fork voting and readiness information.

### Request Parameters

> Sample Request

```shell
curl -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '[]' https://api.oracleminer.com/xrs/xmr_hard_fork_info
```

```plaintext
blocknet-cli xrService xmr_hard_fork_info
```
<code class="api-call">xmr_hard_fork_info</code>

This call does not take parameters.


### Response

<aside class="success">
200 OK
</aside>

> Sample 200 Response

```shell
{
  "credits": 0,
  "earliest_height": 1978433,
  "enabled": true,
  "state": 1,
  "status": "OK",
  "threshold": 0,
  "top_hash": "",
  "untrusted": false,
  "version": 12,
  "votes": 10080,
  "voting": 12,
  "window": 10080
}
```

```plaintext
{
  "reply": {
    "credits": 0,
    "earliest_height": 1978433,
    "enabled": true,
    "state": 1,
    "status": "OK",
    "threshold": 0,
    "top_hash": "",
    "untrusted": false,
    "version": 12,
    "votes": 10080,
    "voting": 12,
    "window": 10080
  },
  "uuid": "29A83109-135A-4F21-8D29-FC6210984755"
}
```

Parameter            | Type          | Description
---------------------|---------------|-------------
credits              | int           | Credits.
earliest_height      | int           | Block height at which hard fork would be enabled if voted in.
enabled              | boolean       | Hard fork is enforced `true`, otherwise `false`.
state                | int           | Current hard fork state. `0` = likely a hard fork, `1` = an update is needed to fork properly, `2` = everything is good.
status               | string        | RPC error code.
threshold            | int           | Minimum percent of votes to trigger hard fork. Default is `80`.
top_hash             | string        | Top transaction hash.
untrusted            | boolean       | Obtained results from bootstrap mode is not trusted (`true`), otherwise trusted (`false`).
version              | int           | The major block version for the fork.
votes                | int           | Number of votes towards hard fork.
voting               | int           | Hard fork voting status.
window               | int           | Number of blocks over which current votes are cast. Default is `10080` blocks.
uuid                 | string        | The response ID, which can be used to view this response again with [xrGetReply](https://api.blocknet.co/#xrgetreply).
